Local actress Mona Monyane has joined popular SABC 1 soapie Skeem Saam, ending her two year television hiatus. The former Muvhango actress announced on social media that she will be taking on the role of Lindiwe Baloyi, a Road Accident Fund Consultant on the show. The star said she was looking forward to embracing the new role, her first after taking some time off to care for her second child with husband, Khulu Skenjana. "It is good to be back doing something different to something people usually know me from but it's still early stages,” she told TshisaLIVE. “It’s been two years since I was on a TV show set and it was exciting to return and flex that bone. I have a great nanny who helps me, so I thought it was the right time to return." There is no better way to announce your comeback than joining one of Mzansi’s favourite soapies, her fans can’t wait for her first appearance.   